02:19.305 --> 02:20.640
♪ SPRING CLEANING! ♪

02:20.723 --> 02:22.225
♪ SPRING CLEANING! ♪

02:22.308 --> 02:23.268
{\an1}Rocko:
HEFF?

02:23.351 --> 02:24.227
HEY, ROCKO.

02:24.310 --> 02:25.895
{\an1}WHY WAS EVERYONE
SINGING?

02:25.979 --> 02:27.856
WE'VE JUST GOT A SONG
IN OUR HEARTS.

02:27.939 --> 02:29.524
HOW DO YOU ALL KNOW THE WORDS?

02:29.607 --> 02:30.525
DID YOU REHEARSE?

02:30.608 --> 02:31.860
YEAH, EVERY THURSDAY.

02:31.943 --> 02:33.528
DIDN'T YOU SEE THE FLYERS?

02:35.280 --> 02:37.073
WELL, HEFF, LET'S
GET THIS GARBAGE

02:37.156 --> 02:38.491
TO THE CITY DUMP.

02:38.575 --> 02:39.576
♪ TO THE DUMP,
TO THE DUMP ♪

02:39.659 --> 02:40.660
♪ TO THE
DUMP-DUMP-DUMP ♪

02:40.743 --> 02:42.120
♪ DUMP-DUMP-DUMP-DUMP! ♪

02:43.663 --> 02:46.207
SORRY, BUD,
THE DUMP IS FULL.

02:46.291 --> 02:47.375
FULL?!

02:47.458 --> 02:48.334
YOU HEARD ME.

02:48.418 --> 02:49.586
BUT WHAT ABOUT
MY GARBAGE?

02:49.669 --> 02:51.254
WHERE WILL IT GO?

02:51.337 --> 02:52.505
HEY! WHAT'S THE HOLD UP?

02:52.589 --> 02:54.591
{\an1}THERE'S NO ROOM
TO DUMP OUR TRASH.

02:54.674 --> 02:56.259
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

02:56.342 --> 02:58.928
THERE'S PLENTY OF ROOM
RIGHT OVER THERE!

02:59.012 --> 03:00.096
(<i> birds singing</i> )

03:00.179 --> 03:02.265
THAT'S A PARK, MR. BIGHEAD.

03:02.348 --> 03:03.433
{\an1}SO WHAT?!

03:03.516 --> 03:05.393
<i>I</i> DON'T USE IT!

03:05.476 --> 03:07.604
{\an1}BUT YOU CAN'T JUST DUMP
YOUR TRASH ANYWHERE.

03:07.687 --> 03:09.856
OF COURSE I CAN.

03:11.274 --> 03:12.775
{\an1}♪ WHAT THE HECK
ARE YOU THINKING? ♪

03:12.859 --> 03:14.360
♪ THESE BARRELS ARE STINKING! ♪

03:14.444 --> 03:16.613
♪ I GOT TO DUMP THIS GOO ♪

03:16.696 --> 03:18.781
♪ BEFORE I BARF AND GAG ♪

03:18.865 --> 03:20.575
♪ IT'S THANKSGIVING
FOR MAGGOTS ♪

03:20.658 --> 03:22.785
♪ GET LOST
BEFORE I DUMP ON YOU! ♪

03:22.869 --> 03:26.289
♪ FISH ARE BRAINLESS FINHEADS ♪

03:26.372 --> 03:29.208
♪ SO I DUMP MY TRASH
IN THE BAY! ♪

03:29.292 --> 03:32.754
♪ BIRDS ARE BIRD-BRAINED
PINHEADS ♪

03:32.837 --> 03:35.715
{\an1}♪ SO MY GUNK INFESTS UP
THEIR FILTHY NESTS ♪

03:35.798 --> 03:38.384
♪ BECAUSE NATURE STINKS ANYWAY ♪

03:38.468 --> 03:41.804
♪ SO I'M SICK OF YOU GLUMPSTERS
SNIFFING MY DUMPSTERS ♪

03:41.888 --> 03:45.141
♪ 'CAUSE CRUD CAN SMELL
LIKE A ROSE ♪

03:45.224 --> 03:48.728
♪ BESIDES THE FILTHY STENCH
WON'T EVEN GET MY ATTENCH ♪

03:48.811 --> 03:51.189
♪ 'CAUSE A TOAD
AIN'T EVEN GOT A NOSE! ♪

03:51.272 --> 03:52.231
(<i> splat</i> )

03:52.315 --> 03:53.608
♪ SO GET OUT OF MY FACE ♪

03:53.691 --> 03:54.817
♪ WHILE I SCUM UP THIS PLACE ♪

03:54.901 --> 03:57.487
♪ WITH MY BEAUTIFUL TOXIC GOO ♪

03:57.570 --> 04:00.782
♪ WISH I COULD SHOOT THIS WASTE
INTO ORBIT IN SPACE ♪

04:00.865 --> 04:03.660
{\an1}♪ SO THE SKY'D BE FILLED
WITH GARBAGE, TOO! ♪

04:03.743 --> 04:04.661
(<i> laughs giddily </i>)

04:04.744 --> 04:06.204
♪ YOO-HOO-HOO! ♪

04:08.498 --> 04:10.500
{\an1}BUT MR. BIGHEAD,
THAT'S NOT VERY GOOD

04:10.583 --> 04:11.793
FOR THE ENVIRONMENT.

04:11.876 --> 04:13.586
WHO CARES ABOUT THE ENVIRONMENT?

04:13.670 --> 04:16.005
{\an1}WE SHOULD
TAKE CARE OF IT.

04:16.089 --> 04:17.257
Man:
THAT'S RIGHT!

04:17.339 --> 04:19.384
ONLY <i> YOU</i> CAN CLEAN UP
THE PLANET.

04:19.466 --> 04:20.635
LOOK, EVERYONE!

04:20.718 --> 04:22.553
IT'S MURKY THE BEAR!

04:22.637 --> 04:23.554
{\an1}NO, NO.

04:23.638 --> 04:24.681
DOWN HERE.

04:24.764 --> 04:26.182
OH!

04:26.265 --> 04:29.435
I MEAN,
CAPTAIN COMPOST HEAP!

04:29.519 --> 04:31.312
SO HOW CAN
WE HELP, C.C.H.?

04:31.396 --> 04:32.522
GLAD YOU ASKED.

04:32.605 --> 04:34.649
{\an1}I JUST HAPPEN TO HAVE
SOME VISUAL AIDS.

04:34.732 --> 04:37.110
FIRST OF ALL...

04:37.193 --> 04:40.405
♪ R-E-C-Y-C-L-E, RECYCLE ♪

04:40.488 --> 04:43.658
♪ C-O-N-S-E-R-V-E, CONSERVE ♪

04:43.741 --> 04:46.035
♪ DON'T YOU P-O-L-L-U-T-E ♪

04:46.119 --> 04:47.495
♪ POLLUTE THE RIVERS,
SKY OR SEA ♪

04:47.578 --> 04:50.456
♪ OR ELSE YOU'RE GONNA GET
WHAT YOU DESERVE ♪

04:50.540 --> 04:53.584
♪ THE OZONE IS IN
HORRIBLE CONDITION ♪

04:53.668 --> 04:56.754
♪ FROM FLUOROCARBONS
IN OUR ATMOSPHERE ♪

04:56.838 --> 05:00.341
♪ THEY ARE TOO SMALL
TO BE SEEN BY NORMAL VISION ♪

05:00.425 --> 05:03.803
{\an1}♪ BUT THERE'S GETTING TO BE
MORE OF US EACH YEAR! ♪

05:03.886 --> 05:07.015
♪ WE COME FROM A VARIETY
OF PLACES ♪

05:07.098 --> 05:10.435
♪ LIKE STYROFOAM CONTAINERS
AND AEROSOL CANS ♪

05:10.518 --> 05:13.730
♪ WE LOVE TO EAT THE OZONE,
IT'S OUR FAVORITE DESSERT ♪

05:13.813 --> 05:20.445
{\an1}♪ AND IF YOU DON'T HAVE AN OZONE
THEN THE SUN CAN REALLY HURT ♪

05:20.528 --> 05:23.573
{\an1}♪ YOU MUST ADMIT
WE MAKE A LOT OF GARBAGE ♪

05:23.656 --> 05:26.951
{\an1}♪ THIS DUMP IS FILLED UP
WAY ABOVE THE BRIM ♪

05:27.035 --> 05:30.079
♪ IF WE DON'T MAKE
AN EFFORT TO RECYCLE ♪

05:30.163 --> 05:32.707
♪ THE FUTURE COULD BE
LOOKING MIGHTY GRIM. ♪

05:32.790 --> 05:34.375
LOOK, IT'S
THE GRIM RECYCLER!

05:34.459 --> 05:36.002
NO AUTOGRAPHS,
PLEASE.

05:36.085 --> 05:38.379
{\an1}♪ SOMEONE'S CUTTING DOWN
THE O-TOWN FOREST ♪

05:38.463 --> 05:41.966
♪ IT'S NOT ENOUGH
TO SIT AROUND AND GRIEVE ♪

05:42.050 --> 05:45.470
{\an1}♪ IF WE DON'T PROTECT
OUR FLORA AND OUR FAUNA... ♪

05:45.553 --> 05:48.097
{\an5}(<i> with German accent</i> ):
THEN WE WON'T HAVE
THE OXYGEN TO BREATHE.

05:48.181 --> 05:49.182
(<i> deep breath</i> )

05:49.265 --> 05:51.434
♪ R-E-C-Y-C-L-E, RECYCLE ♪

05:51.517 --> 05:52.477
RECYCLE!

05:52.560 --> 05:54.145
♪ C-O-N-S-E-R-V-E, CONSERVE ♪

05:54.228 --> 05:55.229
CONSERVE.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.273
♪ DON'T YOU P-O-L-L-U-T-E ♪

05:57.356 --> 05:58.858
♪ POLLUTE THE RIVERS,
SKY OR SEA ♪

05:58.941 --> 06:01.235
♪ OR ELSE WE'RE GONNA GET ♪

06:01.319 --> 06:05.490
All:
♪ WHAT WE DESERVE! ♪

06:05.573 --> 06:08.868
WHAT A SAPPY SONG!

06:08.951 --> 06:10.453
BUT SAPPY AS IT IS

06:10.536 --> 06:12.371
IT STILL MAKES
A GOOD POINT.

06:12.455 --> 06:14.165
{\an1}WHAT DO WE SAY,
EVERYONE?

06:14.248 --> 06:15.792
LET'S CLEAN UP O-TOWN!

06:15.875 --> 06:18.294
HURRAY!

06:30.139 --> 06:31.265
WELL, MR. HEAP

06:31.349 --> 06:32.725
{\an1}PRETTY CLEAN,
ISN'T IT?

06:32.809 --> 06:35.561
WELL, YES AND NO.

06:35.645 --> 06:36.687
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

06:36.771 --> 06:38.439
{\an1}WHO ISN'T
DOING THEIR PART?

06:38.523 --> 06:39.565
THEM!

06:41.901 --> 06:43.486
(<i> liquid gurgling</i> )

06:43.569 --> 06:45.613
CONGLOMO, EH?

06:45.696 --> 06:47.990
WELL, THAT'S
BIG BUSINESS.

06:48.074 --> 06:50.326
(<i> all muttering</i> )

06:50.409 --> 06:52.495
WAIT! WE'RE NOT
GOING TO LET THEM

06:52.578 --> 06:54.205
GET AWAY WITH THIS,
ARE WE?

06:54.288 --> 06:56.749
{\an1}WELL, YEAH.
THAT'S CONGLOMO.

06:56.833 --> 06:58.501
THEY OWN EVERYTHING.

06:58.584 --> 07:00.670
THEY EVEN OWN CITY HALL.

07:00.753 --> 07:02.547
AND YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY.

07:02.630 --> 07:05.341
IT'S GOING TO BE
A SONG, ISN'T IT?

07:05.424 --> 07:08.970
♪ YOU CAN'T FIGHT CITY HALL ♪

07:09.053 --> 07:12.098
♪ YOU CAN'T FIGHT
CORPORATE AMERICA ♪

07:12.181 --> 07:15.309
♪ THEY ARE BIG
AND WE ARE SMALL ♪

07:15.393 --> 07:19.689
♪ YOU CAN'T FIGHT CITY HALL! ♪

07:19.772 --> 07:21.941
I KNOW IT SEEMS LIKE
THE LITTLE PERSON

07:22.024 --> 07:24.443
MAY NOT MAKE MUCH
OF A DIFFERENCE IN THIS WORLD.

07:24.527 --> 07:26.696
BUT IF YOU GET ENOUGH
LITTLE PEOPLE TOGETHER

07:26.779 --> 07:29.282
{\an1}THEN YOU'VE GOT A... A...
OH, WHAT'S THE WORD?

07:29.365 --> 07:30.700
AN UNRULY MOB?

07:30.783 --> 07:31.784
{\an3}YEAH!

07:31.868 --> 07:33.327
I MEAN, NO.

07:33.411 --> 07:35.872
WHAT I MEAN IS,
IF WE ALL BAND TOGETHER

07:35.955 --> 07:38.708
WE'LL BE LIKE
A LARGE GROUP OF PEOPLE

07:38.791 --> 07:40.877
WHO'VE ALL, UM, UM,
BANDED TOGETHER.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.962
OH, THIS ISN'T GOING VERY WELL.

07:43.045 --> 07:44.463
NO, NO, ROCKO, LOOK!

07:44.547 --> 07:46.007
YOU'RE MESMERIZING THEM!

07:46.090 --> 07:48.217
{\an1}WE'VE GOT TO FIGHT
FOR WHAT WE BELIEVE IN!

07:48.301 --> 07:51.137
I SAY WE MARCH DOWN TO
THE CONGLOMO BUILDING RIGHT NOW

07:51.220 --> 07:52.889
AND GIVE THEM
A PIECE OF OUR MINDS!

07:52.972 --> 07:54.182
ARE YOU WITH ME?

07:54.265 --> 07:57.226
I SAID,
ARE YOU WITH ME?

07:57.310 --> 07:59.854
♪ I GUESS WE MIGHT AS WELL. ♪

07:59.937 --> 08:01.397
THAT'S THE SPIRIT!

08:01.480 --> 08:03.900
♪ WE'VE ALL GOT NOTHING
BETTER TO DO ♪

08:03.983 --> 08:07.069
♪ AND THIS DUMP
IS STARTING TO SMELL ♪

08:07.153 --> 08:10.823
♪ SO WE'LL MARCH
DOWNTOWN WITH YOU. ♪

08:13.743 --> 08:15.828
WE DEMAND TO SEE
THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS!

08:15.912 --> 08:17.622
AND YOU WOULD BE?

08:17.705 --> 08:20.124
WE'RE A BIG
UNRULY MOB!

08:20.208 --> 08:24.003
♪ WE'RE A BIG UNRULY MOB. ♪

08:24.086 --> 08:27.632
{\an1}WELL, ACTUALLY, WE'RE THE
CONCERNED CITIZENS OF O-TOWN.

08:27.715 --> 08:29.008
AND YOU WERE
SENT BY?

08:29.091 --> 08:32.094
{\an1}A BIG PILE OF ROTTING
VEGETABLE MATTER.

08:32.178 --> 08:36.349
♪ A GREAT BIG ROTTING PILE. ♪

08:36.432 --> 08:38.183
WELL, A COMPOST HEAP

08:38.267 --> 08:40.727
{\an1}BUT THE DESCRIPTION
IS ACCURATE.

08:40.811 --> 08:43.105
AND DO YOU HAVE
AN APPOINTMENT?

08:43.188 --> 08:47.109
{\an1}THIS WAS SORT OF A SPUR OF
THE MOMENT, SPONTANEOUS THING.

08:47.193 --> 08:49.946
{\an5}UN-HUH. THEN
HOW DO YOU ALL
KNOW THE WORDS?

08:50.029 --> 08:51.113
OOH, BOY.

08:51.197 --> 08:52.657
HE'S GOT YOU
THERE, ROCK.

08:52.740 --> 08:53.950
<i>I</i> DON'T KNOW THE WORDS!

08:54.033 --> 08:55.576
♪ HE DOESN'T KNOW THE WORDS. ♪

08:55.660 --> 08:59.247
SHUT UP!

08:59.330 --> 09:01.958
SORRY, YOU CAN'T GET IN
WITHOUT AN APPOINTMENT.

09:02.041 --> 09:03.543
OH.

09:03.626 --> 09:07.463
♪ I GUESS WE'LL
ALL GO HOME. ♪

09:07.546 --> 09:08.839
NO! WAIT, GUYS!

09:08.923 --> 09:11.050
{\an1}DON'T GIVE ME
THIS APPOINTMENT STUFF.

09:11.133 --> 09:12.802
WE ARE THE CUSTOMERS.

09:12.885 --> 09:15.846
{\an1}IT'S OUR BUSINESS
THAT KEEPS YOUR BUSINESS GOING.

09:15.930 --> 09:19.016
{\an1}SO I <i> INSIST</i> YOU LET ME SPEAK
TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

09:19.100 --> 09:21.143
ALL RIGHT, WHATEVER.

09:21.227 --> 09:22.144
REALLY?

09:22.228 --> 09:23.145
THANKS.

09:23.229 --> 09:24.272
(<i> shoes squeaking</i> )

09:29.735 --> 09:30.820
(<i> clears throat</i> )

09:30.903 --> 09:32.613
MY NAME IS ROCKO.

09:32.697 --> 09:37.702
AND, WELL, I REPRESENT A GROUP
OF CONSUMERS WHO, WELL, UH...

09:37.785 --> 09:40.246
WE'VE JUST NOTICED LATELY
THAT YOUR COMPANY

09:40.329 --> 09:43.833
{\an1}HAS BEEN POLLUTING THE RIVERS
AND DESTROYING THE FORESTS.

09:43.916 --> 09:46.335
{\an1}AND, WE'D LIKE YOU TO,
UH... MAYBE YOU COULD...

09:46.419 --> 09:48.629
R-E-C-Y-C-L-E

09:48.713 --> 09:50.423
{\an1}RECYCLE?

09:50.506 --> 09:51.841
WHY IS HE
SPELLING?

09:51.924 --> 09:53.676
{\an1}THERE'S A CATCHY TUNE
THAT GOES WITH IT

09:53.759 --> 09:55.094
BUT I MISSED THE REHEARSALS.

09:55.177 --> 09:57.555
WELL, MR. ROCKO,
WE'RE RATHER BUSY.

09:57.638 --> 09:59.974
SO IF YOU WOULD JUST
GET TO THE POINT!

10:00.057 --> 10:01.058
THE POINT?

10:01.142 --> 10:03.352
UH, WELL, THE POINT IS...

10:03.436 --> 10:04.854
(<i> banging</i> )

10:04.937 --> 10:07.857
♪ WE'D LIKE TO SEE YOU STOP
ALL THIS POLLUTING ♪

10:07.940 --> 10:10.943
♪ AND TREAT POOR MOTHER NATURE
WITH MORE CARE ♪

10:11.027 --> 10:13.821
♪ WE HOPE THAT YOU DON'T
MIND US ALL INTRUDING ♪

10:13.904 --> 10:16.407
♪ BUT WE'D REALLY LIKE
TO MAKE YOU ALL AWARE ♪

10:16.490 --> 10:19.327
♪ THAT YOU SHOULD ♪

10:19.410 --> 10:21.704
♪ R-E-C-Y-C-L-E, RECYCLE ♪

10:21.787 --> 10:22.997
TOLD YOU
IT WAS CATCHY.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.333
♪ C-O-N-S-E-R-V-E, CONSERVE ♪

10:25.416 --> 10:27.543
♪ DON'T YOU P-O-L-L-U-T-E ♪

10:27.626 --> 10:29.128
♪ POLLUTE THE RIVERS,
SKY AND SEA ♪

10:29.211 --> 10:35.843
♪ OR ELSE YOU'RE GONNA GET
WHAT YOU DESERVE! ♪

10:38.637 --> 10:39.972
(<i> clears throat</i> )

10:40.056 --> 10:41.265
SO WHAT DO YOU SAY?

10:41.349 --> 10:43.184
WILL YOU CLEAN UP YOUR ACT?

10:51.359 --> 10:52.443
OKAY.

10:52.526 --> 10:53.444
REALLY?

10:53.527 --> 10:55.529
♪ ROCKO FOUGHT CITY HALL ♪

10:55.613 --> 10:57.073
AND I WON, TOO!

10:57.156 --> 10:59.867
♪ ROCKO FOUGHT
CORPORATE AMERICA! ♪

10:59.950 --> 11:02.078
♪ THEY WERE BIG
AND HE IS SMALL ♪

11:02.161 --> 11:03.746
BUT NOT <i> TOO</i> SMALL!

11:03.829 --> 11:07.166
♪ ROCKO FOUGHT CITY HALL. ♪

11:07.249 --> 11:11.045
{\an1}OKAY, WHO IS IN CHARGE
OF WASTE DISPOSAL?

11:11.128 --> 11:12.004
AH!

11:12.088 --> 11:13.923
ED BIGHEAD.

11:14.006 --> 11:17.301
GET THAT TOAD UP HERE
ON THE DOUBLE.

11:17.385 --> 11:20.096
HE'S GOT SOME CLEANING TO DO.

11:21.222 --> 11:22.098
(<i> liquid gurgling</i> )

11:25.101 --> 11:26.435
(<i> gasping</i> )

11:26.519 --> 11:27.812
(<i> screaming</i> )

11:30.356 --> 11:31.440
(<i> screaming louder</i> )

11:31.524 --> 11:32.900
(<i> crashes</i> )

11:32.983 --> 11:35.694
(<i> metal clinking</i> )

11:35.778 --> 11:35.861
(<i> clattering</i> )

11:40.199 --> 11:41.909
(<i> knocking at door</i> )

11:44.120 --> 11:45.788
(<i> gasping</i> )

11:45.871 --> 11:47.790
All:
HI, ED!

11:47.873 --> 11:50.251
{\an1}THE WHOLE TOWN WANTED TO EXPRESS
OUR THANKS FOR CLEANING UP.

11:50.334 --> 11:52.461
WE MADE YOU THIS PLAQUE.

11:52.545 --> 11:54.004
PLAQUE, SHMAQUE.

11:54.088 --> 11:56.090
IF IT HADN'T BEEN FOR
YOU LOUSY DO-GOODERS

11:56.173 --> 11:58.092
